Welcome!

Thank you for choosing me!

To install: 

1. Put files out of archive on your desktop.
2. Click My Computer.
3. Click Local Disk (C:).
4. Click Program Files.
5. Click Valve, then Steam.
6. Click SteamApps, then *Your User Name*.
7. Click Counter-Strike Source then the cstrike file.
8. In the cstrike file, find, then click Maps.
9. Highlight and drag the files taken out of the archive that should be placed on your desktop to the current file you have open (Maps).
10. Now the map(s) are able to be played, start-up Counter-Strike and go to Create Server and under the Maps dopdown find the map you got.
11. Now push Start Server and you should be playing the map! 
12. Enjoy.

This is the beta version of my upcomming map, but it is still a great map. Unlike other DE maps this one only has one bombsite, but a second one will be added in the final version. 

There are lots of hiding places and flanking routes (through the vents among other places) while the map still remains quite small with alot of intense fighting. Over its development the map has been playtested alot with up to 8 people and is quite balanced. It also works just fine when playing against bots, although they can not use vents at the time being and thier tactics are fairly limited.

**Please try it / rate it and any feedback would be appreciated!**

UPDATE: I am currently working on a much improved version of this map for CSGO, with two bombsites and with more than half of the areas completely redesigned. Feedback on this map is still apprecitated though!

This is the final release of de_zenith.  It is a fairly straightforward bomb map with two bomb sites.  It is set in a snowy mountainous area.  The Terrorists spawn at the top of a large hill at the end of a ski lift/gondola.

Site A is an inside warehouse-ish area with lots of overhead walkways.  Site B is the staple monument of de_zenith.  It has a large radio tower that is visible throughout the entire map.  The tower does collapse when the bomb goes off.

As with all of my maps, I concentrated on making de_zenith twist on itself many times so ambushes are possible and multiple different routes can be taken.  Although the elevated walkways throughout the map are loud and put you out into the open, they give you very direct, distance cutting paths between the bombsites.

If you have any questions, comments, or concerns, email me at jazzbassking@hotmail.com

Enjoy!
-Oreo
